Applying in October will give students access to the most amount of money!

August 26, 2019 at 9:49 AM ¬∑

For parents, if you are driving your kids to school make sure they are in the appropriate child safety seat and placed in the vehicle according to child passenger safety laws. This means all children 13 and under shall ride in the back seat. üëå

shared_text:
Washington Green Schools
May 29, 2019 at 10:29 AM ¬∑

A big congratulations to Gaiser Middle School of Vancouver Public Schools for earning their Sustaining Platinum certification! Gaiser is the fourth school in the state and the second Clark County Green Schools to reach this level, the highest certification Washington Green Schools offers.

Gaiser's Green Team went big and recertified in all six environmental categories. It is clear the entire school is committed to #sustainability and we are impressed by their work. Go Grizzlies!

post_text: Did you receive yours?
shared_text:
Clark County WA Elections
January 24, 2019 at 2:02 PM ¬∑

Ballots go out in the mail tomorrow to all registered voters in the Evergreen, Hockinson, La Center, Ridgefield and Vancouver School Districts for the upcoming Feb. 12 special election.

If a voter does not receive a ballot by Thursday, Jan. 30, please contact the Elections Office at 564.397.2345 to request a replacement ballot. Replacement ballots also may be requested by email, mail, or in person at the Elections Office, 1408 Franklin St. Office hours are 8 am to 5 pm, Monday through Friday.
